  "text": "An interesting feature of cocoa yellow mosaic virus (CYMV) is its similarity to turnip yellow mosaic virus (TYMV) and wild cucumber mosaic virus (WCMV). Their particles have similar shape, size, external morphology, and sedimentation rates ; moreover, MacLeod [CITATION_1] and MacLeod (personal communication) found that the nucleoprotein particles of all three viruses contain similar amounts of nucleic acid, of similar composition (with 37-40 yo cytidylic acid).",
